    <text>
        <body>
            <div type=”letter”>
                <opener><dateline><date when="1916-10-14">Oct. 14, 1916.</dateline></date>
                    <salute>Dear <persName key="harriet_monroe">Harriet</persName>:</salute></opener>
<p>I enclose a copy of <title key="chinoiseries" level="a">&quot;Chinoiseries&quot;</title>. If you have been looking in <title key="littleReview"level="j">&quot;The Little Review&quot;</title>for it, it is no wonder you could not find it, for it came out in the <date when="1916-07">July</date> number of <title key="others" level="j">&quot;Others&quot;</title>.</p>
                <p>I am most interested to see <title key="newPoetryAnthology" level="m">your &quot;Anthology&quot;</title>. I tried to buy it the other day, and was discouraged to find it was not yet out.</p>
<p>My book <!-- tag this?--> is not out, either. I shall send you a copy as soon as it is.</p>
<p>I am awfully glad you told me about <persName key="mary_aldis">Mrs. Aldis</persName>. I had no idea she had been ill. I am writing to her to ask if she wants to postpone our play.</p>     
                <closer>Affectionately yours,</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
